Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "budala" in different forms and positions:

1. *Budalo*, zašto si to uradio? (Fool, why did you do that?)
2. Nemoj da budeš *budala* i poslušaj me. (Don't be a fool and listen to me.)
3. Rekao sam mu da je *budala* što je otišao tamo. (I told him he was a fool for going there.)
4. Neću da radim sa *budalama* kao što si ti. (I don't want to work with fools like you.)
5. *Budale* ne shvataju ozbiljnost situacije. (Fools don't understand the seriousness of the situation.)
6. Ona me je nazvala *budalom* jer sam pogrešio u računu. (She called me a fool because I made a mistake in the calculation.)
7. *Budale* se često šale na račun drugih ljudi. (Fools often make jokes at the expense of other people.)
8. Ne možeš me prevariti, ne nisam *budala*. (You can't fool me, I'm not a fool.)
9. On je *budalast* kada pije previše alkohola. (He acts foolish when he drinks too much alcohol.)
10. Dečko koji me je ošamario je *budalasti* huligan. (The boy who slapped me is a foolish thug.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "budala" can be considered a derogatory term and should be used with caution.